&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Horace Mann, we are driven by a passion for supporting educators and helping them achieve lifelong financial success. As an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Application Systems Analyst Programmer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will play a critical role in supporting, configuring, and enhancing business applications across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will analyze user issues and enhancement requests, identify root causes, and deliver effective, cost-efficient solutions aligned with business objectives. You will serve as a key liaison between business partners and IT, ensuring systems are reliable, efficient, and user-friendly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for application-related issues and user inquiries&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Troubleshoot, analyze, and document system issues; recommend and implement solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communicate issue status, timelines, and resolutions clearly to stakeholders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide technical support, user guidance, and training as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with data access, reporting, and enabling user self-service capabilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with Business Analysts and Developers to design and implement system enhancements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and execute test plans to validate system changes and ensure quality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support help desk requests and resolve technical issues in a timely manner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain a strong understanding of business processes and supported systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Configure insurance products, workflows, and processing rules&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in an on-call rotation to monitor nightly production cycles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Business Administration, or a related field (or equivalent experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working knowledge of enterprise applications and IT-supported systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to translate technical concepts for non-technical audiences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven ability to collaborate effectively across teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with system testing and release validation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Familiarity with reporting tools and data analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with policy administration or claims systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with LifePRO, Hyland Perceptive, and/or Online ToolWorks SmartBatch&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of insurance products (Annuities, Life, IUL, Supplemental Health, Group Health, Group Life)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with SQL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;collapsed-field-text&quot;&gt;$57,500.00 - $79,100.00&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary is commensurate to experience, location, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;#VIZI&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in; font-family: Cali

&lt;p&gt;At Horace Mann, we are committed to helping educators and their families achieve lifelong financial security. We are seeking a visionary &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Vice President, Chief Life Underwriter&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the strategic direction of our Life underwriting function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the organization&#39;s highest underwriting authority for the Life business, you will establish underwriting philosophy, guide risk selection and mortality management, and champion innovative underwriting practices that enhance the customer and agent experience while protecting the company&#39;s financial strength.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This critical leadership role partners closely with Product, New Business Operations, Distribution, Compliance, reinsurers, and vendor partners to develop and execute underwriting strategies that support profitable growth and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Underwriting Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the highest underwriting authority for the Life business, providing strategic leadership for underwriting philosophy, risk selection, mortality management, governance, and operational effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain underwriting guidelines, authorities, and risk selection practices that balance growth objectives with sound mortality management and regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic direction on complex underwriting cases and emerging underwriting issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovation &amp;amp; Underwriting Transformation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the evolution of the underwriting function through the evaluation and implementation of innovative underwriting methodologies, technologies, and external data sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead initiatives involving accelerated underwriting, predictive analytics, and digital capabilities that improve customer and agent experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement by identifying opportunities to enhance underwriting efficiency, consistency, and decision quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate processing and issuance of Life insurance applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, enhance, and implement underwriting policies, procedures, and operational standards with clearly defined accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with internal underwriting guidelines, regulatory requirements, and legal directives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support organizational initiatives that improve underwriting quality, service levels, and operational performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Partnership &amp;amp; Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Life &amp;amp; Retirement leadership—particularly Product Strategy and Life New Business Operations—to support product innovation and business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Distribution, Compliance, Finance, Technology, reinsurers, and vendor partners to optimize underwriting capabilities and customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with agents, field leaders, and business partners, serving as a trusted underwriting advisor.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Talent Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and develop a high-performing underwriting organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of accountability, collaboration, continuous learning, and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support succession planning, talent development, and performance management for underwriting staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;str

&lt;p&gt;Horace Mann is seeking a strategic and innovative &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Vice President, Life &amp;amp; Retirement Pricing&lt;/strong&gt; to lead pricing, product innovation, and actuarial support for our Life and Retirement business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This strategically important role will serve as a key partner in developing and pricing new products, enhancing existing offerings, and driving profitable growth through actuarial leadership and market-focused innovation. The successful candidate will play a critical role in shaping the future of Horace Mann&#39;s Life and Retirement portfolio while partnering across Product Strategy, Distribution, Operations, Technology, and Actuarial Valuation teams.&amp;nbsp; The individual will also ensure sound actuarial practices and governance standards (ASOPs, Horace Mann policies, and similar) are followed for all processes and activities within the pricing function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines deep actuarial expertise with strong business acumen, leadership capabilities, and a passion for developing innovative solutions that serve educators and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Pricing &amp;amp; Development Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the pricing strategy and actuarial support for new Life and Retirement products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee preliminary pricing analyses and final pricing recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and present product pricing reports, recommendations, and business case analyses to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure pricing methodologies align with profitability objectives, market competitiveness, and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product Strategy to design, develop, and launch innovative Life and Retirement solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate Setting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Life and Retirement rate-setting process, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommendation development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive presentation materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acquiring stakeholder alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Illustration Actuary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the Illustration Actuary for Life products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide actuarial oversight and support for illustration systems and methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure illustrations remain compliant, accurate, and aligned with product objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Actuarial Systems &amp;amp; Technology Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee actuarial support for system development initiatives, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New product implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;System conversions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing and illustration system improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Technology and Operations teams to ensure successful implementation of actuarial requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assumptions &amp;amp; Experience Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with actuarial valuation team on assumption development, experience studies, and profitability assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support long-term business planning through financial modeling, forecasting, and scenario analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide insight into emerging experience trends and their impact on product pricing and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Strategic Influence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing strategic goals and initiatives for the Life &amp;amp; Retirement business.&

&lt;p&gt;At Horace Mann, we know that behind every claim is a customer looking for guidance and support during an unexpected event. We are seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Auto Claims Adjuster II&lt;/strong&gt; to investigate, evaluate, negotiate, and resolve auto claims while delivering an exceptional customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll independently manage a diverse inventory of claims, applying your advanced claims knowledge to determine coverage, investigate liability, evaluate damages, and negotiate fair settlements. The ideal candidate is a collaborative problem solver who thrives in a fast-paced environment and is committed to delivering timely, accurate, and compassionate service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must be flexible to work shift between 7a-7p central time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Claims Investigation &amp;amp; Evaluation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify coverage and investigate liability, damages, and the scope of loss for assigned auto claims.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate claim facts, determine claim value, and negotiate settlements in accordance with company best claim practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate &lt;strong&gt;multi-vehicle accidents&lt;/strong&gt; and other complex loss scenarios while making sound claims decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply state-specific laws, regulations, and company guidelines to ensure accurate claim handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Claims Resolution &amp;amp; Customer Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage an assigned inventory of claims independently while maintaining quality, productivity, and service standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide proactive, transparent, and timely communication to customers, claimants, agents, repair facilities, and other involved parties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver an extraordinary customer experience by demonstrating empathy, professionalism, and ownership throughout the claims process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve customer concerns through effective negotiation and conflict resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal departments and external business partners to facilitate timely claim resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate leadership by sharing knowledge, collaborating with peers, and contributing to a positive team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate claim documentation and ensure compliance with company policies and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously develop technical claims knowledge and stay current on industry trends and state regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2+ years of prior claims handling experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to independently manage an inventory of auto claims while making sound claims decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of insurance coverage, liability investigations, and claims handling practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to obtain and maintain all required &lt;strong&gt;state adjuster licenses&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational, analytical, and problem-solving abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience investigating complex or multi-vehicle accidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership and conflict resolution skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a customer-focused claims environment with responsibility for claim owner

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: AVP Finance Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assistant Vice President Finance Operations owns creating and executing the strategic and operational vision of the Finance Operations functions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You transform the art of the possible into reality by thinking big, bold and across boundaries.&amp;nbsp; Your strategic vision drives process improvements, including the strategic use of outsourcing and technology, to enhance scalability and performance.&amp;nbsp; By leveraging economies of scale, standardizing processes, and optimizing delivery across a mix of internal and external resources you ensure high-quality, reliable data for decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic and operational leadership for the Finance Operations functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement, consistency, and operational excellence across Finance Operations capabilities while promoting efficiency, innovation, and scalability. Consider the strategic use of outsourcing for straight through processing functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key partner to business leaders, leveraging cross-functional expertise to strengthen operational delivery and organizational performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Finance Operations strategies align with corporate goals, customer expectations, and regulatory requirements while maintaining flexibility in delivery models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead modernization initiatives, leveraging digital transformation, optimizing automation, and implementing AI to streamline workflows and improve operational agility, yielding improved efficiency and reduced manual processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transform the art of the possible into reality. Think big, bold and across boundaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benchmark internal performance against industry standards and integrate best practices in internal controls, modernization, and planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adept at presenting ideas clearly and in a compelling manner to senior management as well as large and small audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and inspire high-performing teams across the Finance Operations functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build collaborative relationships with leaders in Finance and throughout the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion a culture of continuous improvement, agility, and operational excellence across all Finance Operations disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with management and other functional directors to reallocate responsibilities dynamically based on organizational priorities and evolving business demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Operations management, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;5+ years&lt;/strong&gt; of experience in Operations, 3+ years in Finance, 5+ years in Leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage complex operations, improving efficiency, and driving insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Robotic Process Automation (RPA) and workflow tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process mapping &amp;amp; reengineering (Lean, Six Sigma)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Soft Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visionary.&amp;nbsp; Tran

